## 3. Button-to-Action Mapping (validated)

All mood identifiers below are confirmed present in `GotchiMoodType`.

| Button | Gotchi call | Extra stat writes (button-layer bonus) | Mood overlays | Action anim |
|--------|-------------|------------------------------------------|---------------|-------------|
| **Wash** | `clean()` | `SATISFACTION +5` | `MOOD_13_CALM` (5s), `MOOD_14_PEACEFUL` (8s) | shader: scrub, 1.5s |
| **Groom** | `interact()` | `HAPPINESS +10`, `FRIEDNSHIP +2` | `MOOD_10_JOYFUL` (5s), `MOOD_52_BEAUTIFUL` (10s) | shader: sparkle, 3s |
| **Feed** | `feed()` | `SATISFACTION +5` | `MOOD_02_SATISFIED` (10s), `MOOD_13_CALM` (5s) | shader: chomp, 3s |
| **Pet** | `interact()` | `HAPPINESS +10`, `LOVE +5`, `FRIEDNSHIP +3` | `MOOD_10_JOYFUL` (8s), `MOOD_30_LOVING` (15s) | shader: warm pulse, 2s |
| **Play** | `play()` | (none; `play()` already does the work) | `MOOD_01_EXCITED` (8s), `MOOD_31_PLAYFUL` (5s) | shader: speed lines, 4s |
| **Give a Break** | `sleep()`/`wake()` | on wake: `HAPPINESS +10` (matches existing `wake()`) | sleep: `MOOD_13_CALM`; wake: `MOOD_12_RELIEVED` | shader: Z-drift/dim, 2s |

**Why `FRIEDNSHIP` (emotional %) and not `SocialStat::FRIENDS` for Groom/Pet:**
`FRIENDS` is a discrete count (`#`). Adding +2/+3 to it per pet means "petting created 3 friends,"
which is nonsense for the display and for any friend-count-based logic on the hex board. Bonding
through touch belongs in the emotional connection stat (`FRIEDNSHIP`). Leave `SocialStat::FRIENDS`
for actual social encounters on the board.

### Button Visual States (unchanged)

| State | Color | Description |
|-------|-------|-------------|
| Normal | RGB(60, 60, 100, 220) | Default |
| Hover | RGB(100, 100, 160, 240) | Mouse over |
| Active | RGB(40, 40, 80, 220) | Being clicked |
| Cooldown | RGB(80, 80, 120, 180) | After use (spam guard) |
| Disabled | RGB(50, 50, 50, 100) | Sleeping or dead |

