## 4. Integration with Gotchi Stats

### 4.1 Action Effects Matrix (button layer + inferred base method)
> Numbers combine what the base method *is claimed to* do (unverified) with the button-layer
> bonuses from section 3. Verify the base-method column against `Gotchi.cpp` before trusting.

| Action | Hunger (`FOOD_LEVEL`) | Energy | Happiness | Excitement | Hygiene (`CLEANLINESS`) | Satisfaction | Other |
|--------|-----------------------|--------|-----------|------------|--------------------------|--------------|-------|
| Wash | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | -> 100 | +5 | — |
| Groom | 0 | 0 | +10 (+15 base) | +20 base | 0 | 0 | `FRIEDNSHIP +2` |
| Feed | -30 base | +10 base | 0 | 0 | 0 | +5 (+10 base) | — |
| Pet | 0 | 0 | +10 (+15 base) | +20 base | 0 | 0 | `LOVE +5`, `FRIEDNSHIP +3` |
| Play | 0 | (drain — see note) | +20 base | +25 base | 0 | 0 | `AGILITY +1` base |
| Give Break (sleep) | 0 | +/tick (tick loop) | +10 on wake | 0 | 0 | 0 | `SLEEP_DEBT` down/tick |

**Energy on Play:** the prior plan asserted `-15` energy on play but the `play()` body is unverified.
Do NOT add a separate `ENERGY -15` in the button layer until you confirm whether `play()` already
drains energy — otherwise you double-drain. Grep `Gotchi.cpp` for `ENERGY` inside `play()` first.

### 4.2 Stats deliberately NOT touched by screen buttons (reserved for hex-board work)
Keeping the screen-button footprint small on purpose. The following are **left untouched here** and
are available for hex-board actions to own:

- `SocialStat::FRIENDS`, `ALLIANCES`, `POPULARITY`, `REPUTATION`, `RESPECT` — social encounters.
- All `SkillStat` (`LEARNING`, `SURVIVAL`, `FORAGING`, `BUILDING`, ...) — exploration/task tiles.
- All `EnvironmentalStat` (`SAFETY`, `TERRITORY`, `HOME`, ...) — world/placement tiles.
- `PhysicalStat` beyond the one `AGILITY` bump from `play()` — training tiles.
- `SecondaryStat::HYDRATION` (Thirst) — a future **Water/Drink** action (screen or board).
- Emotional stats beyond the six in section 2 (`ANGER`, `SADNESS`, `FEAR`, `BOREDOM`, `TRUST`,
  `HOPE`, `CURIOSITY`, `CREATIVITY`, `FOCUS`, `PATIENCE`, `GRATITUDE`, `PEACE`) — event/board driven.

### 4.3 KNOWN RISK: core vs. secondary-alias duplication
`Health/Hunger/Thirst/Energy/Sleep/Hygiene` exist in **two** places:
- `coreStats_[0..5]` (no public enum accessor found in `GotchiStats.cpp`), and
- `secondaryStats_[20..25]` via the `SecondaryStat` aliases `FITALITY/FOOD_LEVEL/HYDRATION/ENERGY/SLEEP_DEBT/CLEANLINESS`.

The public `addStat`/`setStat` API can only reach the **alias** copy. If `feed()`/`clean()`/`heal()`
or the tick loop write `coreStats_` directly, and the DETAILED VITALS display reads the alias (or
vice versa), the button will appear to do nothing or the two values will drift.

**Action item (blocking):** before wiring Feed/Wash, run and paste:
```
grep -n "coreStats_\|secondaryStats_\|FOOD_LEVEL\|CLEANLINESS\|FITALITY" Gotchi.cpp GotchiStats.hpp GotchiScene.cpp
```
Establish which copy is the source of truth for the display, and write to that one.

