## 8. Testing Checklist

### Compile gate (do these FIRST)
- [ ] Handler compiles — confirms `EmotionalStat::FRIEDNSHIP` (misspelled), `LOVE`, `SATISFACTION`,
      `HAPPINESS` and all `MOOD_*` identifiers resolve.
- [ ] Shader compiles on desktop (`#version 330`) AND web (`#version 300 es`).

### Evidence-based verification (paste literal output, no self-certification)
- [ ] `grep -n` in `Gotchi.cpp` for each interaction method's stat writes — reconcile with section 1.
- [ ] Confirm which storage (`coreStats_` vs alias) the vitals display reads (section 4.3).
- [ ] `Feed` lowers the displayed Hunger value (screenshot or log the before/after number).
- [ ] `Wash` sets displayed Hygiene to 100.
- [ ] `Play` does not double-drain energy (log ENERGY before/after; one drain only).

### Behavior
- [ ] Each button triggers its shader overlay for the right duration, drawn on top of the sprite.
- [ ] Mood overlays apply (log `getMoodName()` after each action).
- [ ] Cooldown blocks re-click for 2s with correct message.
- [ ] Dead gotchi: all actions blocked. Sleeping gotchi: only "Give a Break" works (wakes it).
- [ ] Feedback message clears after 3s.

